                     data-val="<h2>Anastasia</h2><p>Date of Birth 21st February 1998</p><p> Both her parents have died and she suffered sexual, emotional and physical abuse at the homesteads where she was sent to stay after the death of her grandmother. She ran away and returned to her homestead where her elder sister was trying to be the teenage head of household but could not afford to care for this youngest child or send her to school as she was working for minimum wage at a factory. Annastasia and her granny had attended the opening of the New Hope Centre and Annastacia had insisted the granny complete the forms to hand her over to our care in the event of her death. The family did not respect this and sent her to live in this other homestead where she was abused and finally ran away. She then insisted her sister bring her to New Hope Centre as her granny had arranged.</p> <p>Anastacia is now over 18 but still needs support as she is studying at Inkhanyeti High School in Manzini.  She is living in Matsapha in a one room flat on her own and learning to manage a monthly budget for food, transport, electricity and rent with her sponsors support.  She is doing well in Form 4 or Grade 11 and persevering her goal to be a neurosurgeon. She no longer has time for dance or music but those talents will wait for the time she comes forth and leads in her destiny.</p>" />
