                     data-val="<h2>Apphia</h2><p>Date of Birth 8th December, 2006</p><p><Apphia’s mother died some years ago, her father continues to battle the health challenges of  HIV/AIDS. Apphia was living with her grandmother in the Bethany community. She was attended our School of Happy Overcomers Preschool. She displayed serious health challenges and woulf hide in the cupboards at school refusing to return home to her grandmother. Our follow-up found a truly unacceptable situation of sexual abuse by neighbours teen and preteen boys. We attempted interventions with police and social welfare but without success until we arranged for her to become part of the Abraham family. permanently and she had a new name and a new life.</p><p>She is now physically well and a brilliant young dancer.  She is in Hope Academy Primary school and doing very well.  She needs continued spiritual, psychological and financial support as she is becoming a happily adjusted child. She is doing well in school and next year will be preparing to participate in October in the All Africa Student Convention in Bloemfontein, South Africa.  </p>">
