                <img src="~/Content/Images/children/xl_Debrah.jpg" style=" height:250px"
                     data-val="<h2>Debrah</h2><p>Date of Birth 12th February, 1994</p><br><p>Both are parents died before Debrah came to New Hope Centre, and she suffered sexual, emotional abuse at the homesteads where she was staying. Young men and other cousins were very cruel to her and she has had much to overcome. Her granny took her in and gave her to New Hope Centre before she died. Debrah has served as an awesome young leader in our home, our camps and Swazi 4-14 Church. She preached her first sermon at the age of 12 in a thanksgiving service at the Lobamba national church to 1600 people, amazing young lady. She is truly a child dedicated to excellence in all she does. Debrah has begun to play the piano. One of her sponsors passed on to heaven and her husband shipped Yvonne’s piano out to Debrah. </p><p> Debrah volunteered in the Jerusalem House of Prayer of All Nations for her gap year and has not looked back.  She returned and ran our children’s home for 6 months as House Manager and then enter Swaziland Theological College for a degree in Theology.  This has catapulted her into an anointing of preaching for new life and revival amongst young people and throughout Eswatini.  Truly she needs support in these years for guidance for anointing and for finances as she prepares herself to be a carrier of God’s glory in the Earth.  Debrah graduated in November 2021 with a bachelor degree from the Eswatini College of Theology.  She is an amazing preacher, prophet and evangelist. She is also amazing on the piano and the harp as she is a worshiper. Psalmist and poet.  She is now serving in full time harp and bowl ministry with Jerusalem house of prayer. She will need support for this commitment for the next four years</p>">
