                    <H2>Keziah</H2><P>Date of Birth 1st September, 2001</P><br><P><br>Keziah’s mother was a widow and worked as a volunteer at New Hope Cente until she died. She had two children Keziah by her husband and another son by an earlier relationship. Keziahs’ grandmother was distraught as she had no means of support these two children now that her daughter had died.  She brought Keziah(her names means the fairest in the land) to come and stay with us. She is a  highly talented and clever young lady having just moved from the Childrens home to the Teenage Girls house. Her grandmother recently passed away which was a big challenge for Keziah as the two of them were great friends.  She wants to be a professional dancer and have her own school of Dance, that is much needed in Swaziland since we have no place at present.  She has persistd and excelled in ballet even leading and motivating other kids only living relative has clever little girl, misses her granny very much but we thank God she was spared of many of the sufferings and abuses that happen once the parents are deceased. She is a delightful, talented in singing and dancing and excelling in primary school.</P>   ">
