                         data-val="<H2>Moriah </H2><P></P><br><P>
                        <br>Moriah is a paternal orphan in that her father is reportedly to have died and left her mother and five siblings destitute. The mother then abandoned the children as she had no means of supporting them or herself. She is alive but is not able emotionally, financially or psychologically to care for her children. Moraih came to New Hope Centre in January 2016 as we were called by Ms Zanele a Former preschool teacher to assist with this destitute family she had come across in the community through her work with Khulisa Umtfana(Raising a Child). along with her younger siblings.  We first worked along side the Social Welfare who wanted the child headed family to remain in their collapsing mud home so that they would not loose their family property since their mother had now been taken by another man.  The three youngsters were collected daily by the New Hope Centre vehicle so they could attend Preschool starting with breakfast, a bath and then school.  We would then return them home in the evenings in our vehicle.  This was costly and cumbersome but God kindly provided through a Californian friend of ours to build them a three room concrete block house for safety from the environment. This ended when the youngest child was accidently burned severly when one of the boys tripped carrying the boiling hot cooking pot and poured this all over the child.  In the morning when we collected them for school this 2 year old was delirious in severe pain and burning fever. Moriah and her brother would not be separated from the little one and screamed and fought us each day trying to remain with Karen at New Hope Centre.  After trying for a few days we informed the Social Welfare workers that this was not workable and we proceeded with taking them officially into New Hope Centre
                        Moriah is a delightful young girl with a passion for art. She finished preschool and struggled with starting literacy and math but we had a volunteer art teacher, Ms Sandy, from Taiwan who opened Moriah’s world of excellence and passion. One day during Shabat Auntie was sharing on how Gods spirit dwells in us when we invite him into our lives and with that suddenly Moriah found herself.  She believed.  She knew in one of those “suddenlies” that if God was in her there was nothing she could not do. She is Now taking music with Mr. Steve, our Music teacher and is pressing forward in all her school work. She has begun to have more confidence and is able to speak and answer questions without breaking down into floods of tears.  Truly God is at work in the redemption of her young life and she needs support financially, socially, prayerfully and spiritually to fulfill her purpose in life. We need your help and request that you [ponder pray and meditate about coming alongside and helping us help her to be who she was created to become, a leader in the midst of many who need help and faith to know they can make it through with God’s help and people’s help.
