                         data-val="  <h2>Tirzah</h2>
                    <p>Date of Birth 10th October, 1994</p> <p>Tirzah and her sister were referred to us by a missionary couple working in the mountains to the north of the country. This couple were work to provide for the orphan care points in the area. The two girls were found to be living totally alone, aged 11 and 6. Tirzah had care for 13 of her relatives who died in the homestead and was doing her best to find means to provide food for her younger sister and to pay for Zipporah to go to preschool in the nearby church.</p>

                    <p>When Tirzah came she knew of no living relatives but after some years her brother and his  wife to be arrived at New Hope Centre. They had traced the family and found that the two little girls were still alive and living in a new home and a new family. This has been an amazing delight and breakthrough for these girls. Tirzah is talented in dance, loves reading and drama, plays the guitar. She wanted to be a medical doctor and her dream was build hospital in her mountainous home region so no other child or person would suffer with no medical help or advice ever again. She has completed high school locally but did not reach the required scores for medical school.  She has enrolled in Fashion Design and is preparing herself to have her own Fashion Business in the years to come so that she can support herself and influence future designs and styles.</p>
