                    <img src="~/Content/Images/children/xl_Titus.jpg" style=" height:250px"
                         data-val="   <h2>Titus</h2>
                    <p>Date of Birth 24th December, 2003</p><p>He is a paternal orphan as his mother is alive, although she was very sick with HIV/AIDS. One day Titus mother was in town after visiting the hospital and saw our red Toyota venture at the post office. She then began asking people around to find out what was this New Hope centre that had the scripture about “out of the mouth of babes and infants, you have ordained praise to silence the avenger.” She then followed the vehicle to find us and begged us to take her two little boys as she was sure she would not live long enough to raise them. Tandzi went with the driver to their home and found the two little boys were extremely sick and near death themselves. Titus’s brother is Timothy. Titus came to us a very sick little boy and we had to quarantine them as they were sick with tuberculosis. We thank God for the timely intervention and the amazing medication that dealt with the physical challenges. </p><p>Today he has overcome and is a tough, energetic strong young man who excells in everything he does. He loves to read, to draw, to play soccer especially in defense as he is the star Goal keeper.  He is always willing t serve and help with his siblings or any tasks we need for the successful care of children in our home and in the schools we go out to visit or the communities where we lead Children’s Church. He wants to be a dentist and is currently studying at Kobe Advanced Academy in Ezulwini about 20Km(10 miles) from our home.  This will be a long process but as God helps him and the family of God through sponsors helps him, he will be a compassionate careful and superb thorough dentist.</p>  ">
