                    <img src="~/Content/Images/children/xl_Zadok.jpg" style=" height:250px"
                         data-val=" <h2>Zadok</h2>
                    <p>Date of Birth 24th May, 2000</p> <p>Zadok is from our Bethany community and started in preschool with us. He is a double orphan though he does have extended family of uncles and aunts. He developed a serious problem in his health as he entered puberty and required special surgery in South Africa.  We thank God for providing through Susan Page and others for supplying the funds for this surgery which was a great success and to Audrey and Howard Emmet for allowing us to stay in their home during the days of this surgery. He has done very well in school and was nominated with Samuel to represent Africa at the All Africa Student Convention in the USA. He is a good thinker and manager.  In his early years he wanted to be an accountant, but he is a boy’s boy. He used to lead the games boys play like sword fights, soccer, pillow fights. He has outgrown that now.  He has an incredible ability to draw and to hear from God with revelation knowledge. He wants to play soccer as a sport but one day be a pastor and he will be an excellent one at caring for people deeply. He is training as a swim coach at present but hopes to complete his high school in South Africa so that he has more options for tertiary education. </p> ">
