                <a href="#" class="pop">
                    <img src="~/Content/Images/children/xl_Zeruiah.jpg" style=" height:250px"
                         data-val="   <h2>Zeruiah</h2>
                    <p>Date of Birth 21st May, 2008</p><P>This little girl was found by our community worker not far from our home. She was living with her grandmother, her grandmother’s friend and her older brother. She was not coping very well with life, her health was poorly.  Her grandmothers friend passed away and they had become homeless, but worse yet the grandmother was an alcoholic and infected with HIV.  The prospects were not good and the details of the circumstances were vague. We processed to take the two young children before the grandmother passed away, which would leave them totally stranded.</P>

                    <p>She and her brother began preschool at the Happy Overcomers Preschool though Zeruiah appeared too weak to walk.  One day she fell of the little plastic chair and hit her head and this precipitated Seizures.  Thankfully Dr Roger Paholka of Ohio and his team of students were on site and he was able to examine her. This began a long road of testing and medication to determine how best to care for her.  She needs a carer with her 24/7 plus we have needed to train our children and our volunteers how to care for her.  Dr Paul Rothwell sponsored her to go for special training that significantly helped her but she still has need of more special education and a healing miracle. Her care is costly and it is our constant prayer that she will be healed.  We have learned that seizures are induced by overheating like if it is a hot day or if she has a fever, or by physical injury. It is as if the brain enters a panic of sorts not emotionally only but physically.  We praise God that most of the time we manage her but she is eleven years old and vulnerable. She has learned to focus and learned to walk on her own since being with us at New Hope Centre but she needs much prayer, care, patience, love and help to make it into her calling. We believe she will one day be like John the Baptist preparing the way for the revelation of the Kingdom of God in our midst.</p>
